CynicalCetus 11/10/2024 6:47 PM
The distant roar of the Capitol hovercraft reverberates through the training center, signaling to all the tributes that the time has come. The tributes are shuffled through the cold, steel corridors towards the gaping mouth of the hovercraft's door. They take their seat. The air is frigid with coolant with the bite of oil and iron. An attendant takes Cetus' paw and the otter yelps in pain as a large iron syringe is injected into his forearm. 'Your tracker.' She mutters. From henceforth, the tributes are now fully beneath the Capitol's purview. Their location, their movement, even their blood pressure and heart rate. The tracker will be there to record the flooding of DMT in their brain when they perish, signalling to the Capitol to prepare a cannon for their demise. Cetus misliked this notion that even 'till his last seconds, he belonged to the Capitol. There was nothing he could do but wait out the cold, silent ride in the hovercraft as they made their way to the arena. (edited)
